In the US state of Oregon, two farmers have turned themselves in to police, and have been moved to a federal facility in California.

Their plight has inspired members of self-styled armed militias to occupy a government property and are refusing to leave.

Al Jazeera\'s Alan Schauffler reports from Burns.


